  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "To add multiple WordPress sites in GoDaddy's Deluxe hosting plan, follow these steps:\n\n1. Log in to your GoDaddy account\n\n2. Navigate to your Hosting dashboard\n\n3. Click on \"Manage\" for your Deluxe hosting plan\n\n4. Go to the \"Websites\" section\n\n5. Click \"Add Website\"\n\n6. Choose \"WordPress\" as your website type\n\n7. Enter your new domain name or use a subdomain\n\n8. Follow the WordPress installation wizard\n\n9. Repeat the process for each additional site you want to add\n\nImportant notes:\n- The Deluxe hosting plan allows multiple websites\n- Each site will need its own domain or subdomain\n- You can install WordPress multiple times on the same hosting account\n- Make sure you have enough resources for multiple sites\n- Consider performance and potential additional costs\n\nPro tips:\n- Use cPanel for easier management\n- Keep WordPress and plugins updated\n- Consider using separate databases for each site\n- Monitor your hosting resources to ensure smooth performance\n\nIf you encounter any issues, contact GoDaddy support for specific assistance.",
